article.headline: Wichita State 72, Austin Peay 62
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Jamar Howard scored 15 points as Wichita State ended Austin Peay's 29-game home winning streak with a 72-62 victory on Saturday. Wichita State (2-0) trailed 15-8 early in the first half before a 10-0 run capped by Kyle Wilson's layup put the Shockers up for good. Despite never retaking the lead, Austin Peay (1-3) never let the game get out of hand. The Governors went on a 7-2 run late in the second half to cut it to 62-58 on a free throw by Will Durden, but couldn't come any closer. Wilson finished with 14 points and nine rebounds, Randy Burns scored 13 and Paul Miller had 11. Austin Peay's Maurice Hampton had a game-high 20 points, while Zac Schlader had 11 points and seven rebounds.
